Description: Our flight northwards from Da Nang to Hanoi.
Temple next to the Cham Museum in Da Nang.

The Museum of Cham Sculpture in Da Nang contains the greatest concentration of art from the Hindu Champa culture that flourished in central and southern Vietnam from broadly the 5th to the 15th century. The museum is not large but its several galleries contain an impressive display of statuary and carvings from various sites in the centre of the country, including sculptures of fanciful beasts and Hindu deities that would have once adorned temples. We did not linger in Da Nang city itself but it was well worth pausing here to visit this fine museum. en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Museum_of_Cham_Sculpture

Photo Title: DSVN D11H-346 with express train S7 Hanoi-Saigon at Danang station.
Description:
D11H-346 is the 'fresh' locomotive for the express train S7 Hanoi-Saigon. The train arrived in this terminus station from the north with a D12E and this is replaced by the D11H for the next few hundred kilometres due south. (I did not see the D11H as far south as Nha trang or so. They only seem to operate around Danang).

Class D11H are built by FAUR in Romania and are a large 1000mm gauge version of the Bulgarian classes 76 and 77,  that run on that country's 760mm gauge lines.


40618 DSVN D11H-346 S7 Danang 10042003

Photo Title: Where Romanian locomotives meet in Vietnam... Two DSVN D11H at Danang station.
Description:
D11H-346 is the 'fresh' locomotive for the express train S7 Hanoi-Saigon. The train arrived in this terminus station from the north with a D12E and this is replaced by a D11H for the next few hundred kilometres due south. (I did not see the D11H as far south as Nha trang or so. They only seem to operate around Danang).

On the left we see D11H-340 with a local train. 'Local' meaning it is not an express train over the complete Hanoi-Saigon route. 

Class D11H are built by FAUR in Romania and are a large 1000mm gauge version of the Bulgarian classes 76 and 77,  that run on that country's 760mm gauge lines.

Photo Title: Oude stoomlokomotief 141-206 Da Nang Station, Vietnam  15 februari 2007

Description: In Danang tref ik bij het depot van weg en werken deze dieselmechanische D2M (Sovjet type Tu6; D4H is de hydraulische TU7)
Even om de hoek kijken... Bij de werkplaats in Dang, uit het zicht van de gewone reizigers, staan wraks van D4Hs.
D4H-560 is de stationsrangeerlok van Danang.

Dankzij de aardige wisselwachter aan het begin van station Danang kon ik ook hier de kartcontrole omzeilen en probleemloos het emplacement opkomen om foto's te maken. Gewone reizigers moesten nog binnen in het station wachten tot de perrons open gingen :-)
Even het vloerkleedje van de D4H luchten...
Ik kon een paar keer op de D4H langs de voor reizigers nog niet toegankelijke perrons van station van Danang rijden.
Ondertussen had de D4H een lange goederentrein met containerwagens samengesteld.
Nog meer rangeren.
Rangeren in Danang.
De traditionele hurkzit van de Vietnamezen hou ik niet zo lang vol als deze DSVN-medewerker.

Tijdens het rangeren in Danang moet de D4H met de lange goederentrein uithalen over de wisselstraat aan de achterkant van het station. Daar loopt nog een oud spoortje naar de haven, dat alleen nog lange rangeerbewegingen gebruikt wordt.

Ik wordt uitgenodigd op de stuurstand van een D11H: mijn favoriete DSVN-lok omdat deze is afgeleid van de diesellokomotiven van de Rodophenlijn in Bulgarije (serie 76 en 77; ook gebowud door FAUR in Boekarest echter 760mm ipv 1000mm spoorwijdte).

Danang is the place to be om de serie D11H te spotten.

40529 DSVN 2x D11H  Danang 10042003

Two train are ready for departure at Danang station. D11H-346 heads the S7 express train from Hanoi to Saigon. The locomotives are exchanged every few hundred kilometres and this one has just been coupled to the S7 express. This long train blocks the passage for passengers to and from the "local"  train with D11H-350, which is visible on the left.

Class D11H are built by FAUR in Romania and are a large 1000mm gauge version of the Bulgarian classes 76 and 77,  that run on that country's 760mm gauge lines.


40606 DSVN D11H-346 S7 + D11H-340 Danang 10042003

Photo Title: DSVN D11H-340 (FAUR) with a local train at Danang

Description:
The driver empties the tea pot in preperation for his upcoming duties. Locomotive D11H-346 from Danang MPD heads the express train S7 further due south.

40601 DSVN D11H-346 theepot Danang 10042003
D12E met trein S7 (Ha Noi - Saigon) loopt station Danang binnen.
Om trein S7 over de wolkenpas tussen Hue en Danang te krijgen, was de hulp van deze D19E als opdruklok nodig.
Tot mijn verbazing komt vanachter de muren van depot Danang deze gloednieuwe D19E naar buiten rollen. De lok is gebouwd in China en voor mijn bezoek wist ik niet van het bestaan van dit type af.
